# Flutter / Dart style

## Files
- `snake_case.dart` filenames.
- One public class per file (allow tightly-coupled private ones in same file).

## Models (Freezed)
```dart
@freezed
class Poi with _$Poi {
  const factory Poi({
    required String id,
    required String name,
    required PoiCategory category,
    required LatLng location,
    String? address,
    @Default(0) double rating,
    @Default(0) int reviewCount,
  }) = _Poi;

  factory Poi.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) => _$PoiFromJson(json);
}
```

## Repositories — write methods return `Either<Failure, T>`
```dart
Future<Either<Failure, void>> addReport(StationCommunitySubmitInput input) async {
  try {
    await _firestore.collection('stationCommunityReports').add(...);
    return const Right(null);
  } on FirebaseException catch (e) {
    return Left(Failure.firestore(e.message ?? e.code));
  } catch (e) {
    return Left(Failure.platform(e.toString()));
  }
}
```

## Riverpod
- `ref.watch(provider)` inside `build()`.
- `ref.read(provider.notifier)` for actions inside callbacks.
- Use `.family.autoDispose` for entity-scoped providers (key: stationKey / poiKey / tripId).
- Use `AsyncValue.when(data:, loading:, error:)` — never `.value!`.

## Widgets
- Prefer `StatelessWidget`. Promote to `ConsumerWidget` / `ConsumerStatefulWidget` when reading providers.
- No business logic in `build()`.
- Use `AppColors`, `AppTextStyles`, `AppTheme`. No raw `Colors.*`, no inline `TextStyle(...)`.
- Always `const` constructors where possible.

## Errors
- Never throw raw strings to UI. Always go through `Failure` taxonomy.
- Map errors to actionable CTAs:
  - `permission` → "Open settings"
  - `network` → "Retry now"
  - `firestore`/`index` → "Try again shortly"
  - `quota` → "Limit reached — wait a bit"

## Comments — DO NOT
```dart
// ❌ Increment the counter
counter += 1;
```

## Comments — DO
```dart
// Dart's [Firebase.apps] can lag behind native; the OS may already have registered
// [DEFAULT] from GoogleService-Info / google-services.json. Hot restart can also
// leave the native app alive while Dart runs main() again.
try {
  await Firebase.initializeApp(...);
} on FirebaseException catch (e) {
  if (e.code != 'duplicate-app') rethrow;
}
```

## After model changes
Run: `dart run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs`
